    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-21T03:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-21T03:00:00-05:00" n="742"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d742">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.154/366: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gauss</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-21T15:00:00+07:00"
                            >August 21, 1941—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received August 22—6:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>360. For Currie from Arnstein: Generalissimo has decided against Holmes due to
                    his nationality. Present contemplated plan is Chinese managing director with
                        Wilson<note n="76" xml:id="d742fn1">Capt. James Wilson, U. S. A., Assistant
                        Military Attaché in China.</note> in complete charge of operation and
                    maintenance of all the lend-lease trucks. Wilson will assume duties as soon as
                    he is released from the Army. [Arnstein.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gauss</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
